But you mentioned, for example, the Trump children.

26
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:36,520
You're talking about Don and Eric are in these chats, getting right into what the talking point should be.

27
00:01:36,860 --> 00:01:39,180
I was in one in which Eric was in one, yes.

28
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:41,000
And who's in charge of all this?

29
00:01:41,020 --> 00:01:43,420
You say coordinated, like who is the person pulling all the strings?

30
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:51,080
So members of the administration, people like James Blair, who run messaging for the admin and the White House and the campaign.

31
00:01:51,300 --> 00:02:00,900
And there's also people who run these consulting houses, these right wing consulting houses that push a lot of this out because they have some plausible deniability and they can hide the money.

32
00:02:01,140 --> 00:02:05,980
So once the money goes from the campaign to the consulting house, they can then distribute it to the influencers.

33
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:08,020
And it's not on any FEC report.

34
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:18,060
So what you're basically saying is when I see a MAGA person online take any position, my starting point should be, is this really his position or did it come from the White House?

35
00:02:18,140 --> 00:02:20,420
Is this really his position or was he paid for it?

36
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:21,360
Correct.

37
